    <riskPattern uuid="c522070a-6f8f-4453-8b03-bcd3f8cae3f2" ref="right-to-correct" name="Right to correct" desc="">
      <tags/>
      <weaknesses/>
      <countermeasures>
        <countermeasure ref="implement-process-to-support-right-to-correct-process" name="Implement process to support &quot;right to correct&quot; process" platform="" cost="0" risk="0" state="Recommended" library="" source="MANUAL">
          <desc>&lt;p&gt;User have the right to request that any stored and inaccurate data be amended.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Businesses should designate two methods for submitting correction requests.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Business has 45 days to respond. Longer timelines are permitted if the business has contacted the end user and provided notification.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The business may deny the request if:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
 &lt;li&gt;The business cannot verify the user's identity to complete the request&lt;/li&gt;
 &lt;li&gt;The request is manifestly unfounded or excessive&lt;/li&gt;
 &lt;li&gt;The information is publicly available information, certain medical information, consumer credit reporting information, or other types of information exempt from the CCPA&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;</desc>
