    <riskPattern uuid="6dd960bb-8ab0-4d5a-b2c7-0a0e4aefaa9f" ref="right-to-non-discrimination" name="Right to Non-discrimination" desc="">
      <tags/>
      <weaknesses/>
      <countermeasures>
        <countermeasure ref="review-business-process-for-discriminatory-processes" name="Review business process for discriminatory processes" platform="" cost="0" risk="0" state="Recommended" library="" source="MANUAL">
          <desc>&lt;p&gt;Businesses cannot deny goods or services, charge a different price, or provide a different level or quality of goods or services just because a user exercised their rights under the CCPA.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;However, if users refuse to provide their personal information to a business or ask it to delete or stop selling their personal information, and that personal information or sale is necessary for the business to provide users with goods or services, the business may not be able to complete that transaction.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Businesses can also offer users promotions, discounts and other deals in exchange for collecting, keeping, or selling their personal information. But they can only do this if the financial incentive offered is reasonably related to the value of the personal information. If users ask a business to delete or stop selling &amp;nbsp;personal information, users may not be able to continue participating in the special deals they offer in exchange for personal information. If &amp;nbsp;users are not sure how the request may affect their participation in a special offer, ask the business.&lt;/p&gt;</desc>
          <implementations/>
          <references/>
